//! Generated catalog foreign-key data: a 1:1 transcription of
//! `sys_fk_relationships[]` from `src/include/catalog/system_fk_info.h` (itself
//! generated by `genbki.pl`), and the builder that renders it into
//! [`CatalogForeignKeyRow`]s for the `catalog_foreign_keys` data seam.
//!
//! Each entry is `(fk_table, fk_columns, pk_table, pk_columns, is_array,
//! is_opt)` exactly as in the header. The `{a, b}` brace literals are the C
//! strings that `pg_get_catalog_foreign_keys()` (misc.c:539/544) feeds to
//! `array_in` to build `text[]` values; [`build_sys_fk_rows`] reproduces that
//! `array_in` for these identifier-only literals (strip the braces, split on
//! commas, trim ASCII whitespace) without an fmgr dispatch.

